Joel Masutha was on Monday fired as Black Leopards coach with immediate effect. SunSport has learnt that Masutha was shown the door with immediate after they landed from their 3-1 loss to Cape Town City FC at the Cape Town Stadium on Sunday. Names of other coaches have been bandied about as possible replacement. Leopards are currently in 14th place on the PSL log with nine points from 11 matches. The Venda outfit were promoted to the PSL after they won the play-offs under Masutha.